We start by recalling the formulas used:

1. Free Cash Flow (FCF) = Operating Cash Flow – Capital Expenditures  
  • In our cash flow, Operating Cash Flow is given as –5,714,107.45 and the Purchase of Fixed Assets (representing capex) is 1,446,972.73.  
  • FCF = –5,714,107.45 – 1,446,972.73 = –7,161,080.18

2. Return on Assets (ROA) = Net Profit / Average Total Assets  
  • Total Assets on 2023-12-31: 13,000,000.00  
  • Total Assets on 2024-01-31: 14,066,175.95  
  • Average Total Assets = (13,000,000.00 + 14,066,175.95) / 2 = 13,533,087.975  
  • Net Profit = –1,669,849.77  
  • ROA = –1,669,849.77 / 13,533,087.975 ≈ –0.1234 = –12.34%

3. Return on Equity (ROE) = Net Profit / Average Owner’s Equity  
  • Owner’s Equity on 2023-12-31: 13,000,000.00  
  • Owner’s Equity on 2024-01-31: 11,330,150.23  
  • Average Owner’s Equity = (13,000,000.00 + 11,330,150.23) / 2 = 12,165,075.115  
  • ROE = –1,669,849.77 / 12,165,075.115 ≈ –0.1373 = –13.73%

4. Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio = Operating Cash Flow / Net Profit (taking absolute values to get a positive ratio)  
  • Ratio = 5,714,107.45 / 1,669,849.77 ≈ 3.42

5. Net Profit Margin = Net Profit / Total Revenue  
  • Net Profit = –1,669,849.77  
  • Total Revenue = 6,920,513.79  
  • Net Profit Margin = –1,669,849.77 / 6,920,513.79 ≈ –0.2413 = –24.13%

6. Gross Profit Margin = Gross Profit / Total Revenue  
  • Gross Profit = 1,340,513.79  
  • Total Revenue = 6,920,513.79  
  • Gross Profit Margin = 1,340,513.79 / 6,920,513.79 ≈ 0.1936 = 19.36%

Thus, our final answer is:

  }
